cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about improving machine translation using neural attentional models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for reranking, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the improvement of grammatical correctness, which is related to neural network models for natural language generation (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the machine translation system using objective and subjective measures, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
